    public interface BusinessObjectModule
    Business object modules are administration objects that can be transported from one system to another. It defines the contractual agreement needed to be defined for each business object module.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String getName()
      Gets the name of the business object module which can be used to uniquely identify different BOM implementations with same offset and same business object type.
      int getOffset()
      Gets the offset order of the component.
      BusinessObjectType getType()
      Gets the business object module type.
